This paper deals with unsupervised segmentation and clustering of speech, which is a problem in natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of Bayesian models and heuristic techniques, which are related to statistical learning (cs.SD) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of fixed-dimensional acoustic word embeddings, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper discusses the scalability of the proposed method, which is related to systems and control (cs.SY).
